The Togolese government has been working to reduce the number of unsafe abortions by providing free contraception and family planning services. However, the government has not yet legalized abortion, and the country’s penal code still criminalizes abortion.

In 2017, the Togolese government passed a law that would allow women to have abortions if their lives were in danger. However, the law was never implemented.
